## FAQ

**Q: I'm an individual prepper. Do I need to pay?**
A: No. Personal use is free under the Community License.

**Q: I want to sell hardware with GridDown. What do I need?**
A: A Commercial License. Contact licensing@blackdot.tech.

**Q: Can I modify GridDown and keep changes private?**
A: Under GPL v3, distributed modifications must be open source. Under Commercial License, you may keep modifications proprietary.

**Q: I'm a SAR volunteer. Which license?**
A: Personal device use is free. Organizational deployment requires Commercial License.

**Q: Can I fork GridDown?**
A: Yes, but forks must be GPL v3 licensed. You cannot sell a fork without a Commercial License.

